  "prompt": "What is the best way to discover what I want in my future?",
  "response": "Here are some effective strategies to help you discover what you want in your future:\n\n1. Self-reflection\n- Journal about your passions and interests\n- Analyze your strengths and values\n- Consider what truly makes you happy\n\n2. Explore different experiences\n- Try new hobbies\n- Take classes or workshops\n- Travel and meet diverse people\n- Volunteer in different settings\n\n3. Personal assessment\n- Take career aptitude tests\n- Consult with a career counselor\n- Complete personality assessments\n- Identify your core values\n\n4. Goal-setting techniques\n- Create short-term and long-term goals\n- Use visualization exercises\n- Practice setting SMART goals (Specific, Measurable, Achievable, Relevant, Time-bound)\n\n5. Network and seek advice\n- Talk to mentors\n- Connect with professionals in fields you're curious about\n- Attend networking events\n- Ask people about their career journeys\n\n6. Experiment and be open-minded\n- Intern or job shadow\n- Take low-risk career risks\n- Be willing to change direction\n- Learn from failures and experiences\n\n7. Invest in personal development\n- Read books about career and personal growth\n- Take online courses\n- Attend personal development workshops\n- Practice continuous learning\n\nRemember, discovering your path is a journey, not a destination.",
